<body>
{{> navbar}}
<script>HighlightTab("faq")</script>

<div class = "background"><br><br>
    <div class="container mt-40">
        <div class = "faq-header">
            <h1>FAQs</h1><br>
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row mt-20 tiles-container">
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                <div class="circle-tile ">
                    <div class="circle-tile-heading pink"><h1><b class="center">1</b></h1></div>
                    <div class="circle-tile-content white">
                        <div class="circle-tile-content">
                            <p><b>How can I adopt an animal from PAWSter Care?</b></p>
                            Applicants go through a screening process to ensure that our rescued animals go to loving homes. The process includes a meet-and-greet with your prospective pet, three (3) separate visits to bond and get to know your chosen animal, and finally, an ocular inspection of your home.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                <div class="circle-tile ">
                    <div class="circle-tile-heading blue"><h1><b class="center">2</b></h1></div>
                    <div class="circle-tile-content white">
                        <div class="circle-tile-content">
                            <p><b>How can I volunteer for PAWS?</b></p>
                            PAWSter Care often needs people to come and help with animal care, but volunteers may also be asked to do out-of-shelter tasks. Volunteers are always welcome as long as you have the right qualities and attitude of being responsible.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                <div class="circle-tile ">
                    <div class="circle-tile-heading green"><h1><b class="center">3</b></h1></div>
                    <div class="circle-tile-content white">
                        <div class="circle-tile-content">
                            <p><b>Do I need to create an account to be able to adopt a dog?</b></p>
                            Yes. A PAWSTer Care account is necessary for people to be able to submit an adoption form. After submitting, the PAWSter Care Team would then decide on approving or disapproving the request.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                <div class="circle-tile ">
                    <div class="circle-tile-heading yellow"><h1><b class="center">4</b></h1></div>
                    <div class="circle-tile-content white">
                        <div class="circle-tile-content">
                            <p><b>How will I know if my request to adopt has been approved?</b></p>
                            After submitting an adoption form, we will contact you in regard to the dog that you wish to adopt. You may also reach out to us directly for a follow up on your pending request.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                <div class="circle-tile ">
                    <div class="circle-tile-heading purple"><h1><b class="center">5</b></h1></div>
                    <div class="circle-tile-content white">
                        <div class="circle-tile-content">
                            <p><b>How do I meet a pet I see on PAWSter Care?</b></p>
                            Once you find a pet you’re interested in adopting, you’ll probably want to meet him or her. Go to the Meet The Dogs page and click on the pet’s picture and this will take you to the pet’s detail page. </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                <div class="circle-tile ">
                    <div class="circle-tile-heading orange"><h1><b class="center">6</b></h1></div>
                    <div class="circle-tile-content white">
                        <div class="circle-tile-content">
                            <p><b>Why wasn't I approved to adopt a dog?</b></p>
                            Here in PAWSter Care, we have sets of Policies and Protocols that we follow and if atleast one of those were not met, you may not adopt a dog. We hope you won’t let this one experience change your mind about providing a loving home to a pet in need. Thank you for helping an adoptable pet and we wish you the best of luck in your search to find a new member of your family.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

